==First round==
{{main|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF first round}}

The bottom four CONCACAF teams, ranked 29 to 32 based on the [[FIFA Men's World Ranking|FIFA rankings]] of December 2023, were divided into two matchups to be played on a [[Two-legged tie|two-legged]] home-and-away basis. The pairings were predetermined, with the 29th ranked team facing the 32nd ranked team, and the 30th ranked team facing the 31st ranked team. The two winners advanced to the second round.<ref name="CONCACAF format"/>
{{:2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF first round}}

==Second round==
{{main|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF second round}}

The draw took place on 25 January 2024 in [[Zürich]], Switzerland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/world-cup-qualifying-men/article/draw-reveals-groups-for-second-round-of-concacaf-world-cup-qualifiers/|title=Draw reveals groups for second round of Concacaf World Cup Qualifiers|publisher=[[CONCACAF]]|date=25 January 2024|access-date=26 January 2024}}</ref>

The top twenty-eight CONCACAF teams in the [[FIFA Men's World Ranking|FIFA rankings]] of December 2023 entered in the second round, joined by the two winners of the first round. Teams were drawn into six groups of five teams and played single [[round-robin tournament|round-robin]] matches (two home and two away). The six group winners and six group runners-up advanced to the third round.<ref name="CONCACAF format"/>

